news.title: Property of tax defaulters to be confiscated in city: Patna civic body
news.para: The defaulters include Maharaja Complex, Patliputra Builders, Patliputra Nirvana, Patliputra Exotica, several shops and houses in Digha-Ashiana area, Patliputra Colony, Biscomaun Colony, Transport Nagar and Maurya Colony localities.

news.title: Vedanta, Welspun among 29 bidders in fray for Mittal Corp
news.para: In 2016, lenders had attempted to sell the company to a strategic buyer by converting its debt into 51% equity under the then prevailing strategic debt restructuring scheme approved by the Reserve Bank of India.

news.title: About 40 high-rises sealed for want of BU nod: Government to Gujarat HC
news.para: The state urban development and urban housing department informed the high court about the action taken pursuant to directions issued on February 15.

news.title: Kolkata civic body check on ponds before building plan nod
news.para: Mayor Firhad Hakim agreed to such a proposal from at least two members, mayor-in-council, during a meeting at the civic headquarters held on Thursday.

news.title: Application deadline for DDA special housing scheme ends
news.para: The last date to apply for its Special Housing Scheme 2021 was March 10. People can apply till midnight, a senior official said. Previously, the last date to apply for the scheme was February 7.

news.title: Families in four Chintels Paradiso towers refuse to vacate flats before structural audit
news.para: The district administration had recently directed the developer to shift 100 flat owners of towers E, F, G and H to alternative accommodations after the residents complained of poor construction quality.

news.title: Builders seek housing ministry's intervention on rising cement, steel prices
news.para: Developers’ body NAREDCO suggests measures to rein in raw material price surge that is putting upward pressure on cost of construction

news.title: Indiabulls Housing Finance moves NCLT against Subhash Chandra to recover loans
news.para: It has claimed that Chandra provided a guarantee for a loan to Gnex Projects that obtained a Rs 190 crore loan from Indiabulls Housing Finance in September 2020 alongwith Essel Home, which was the co-borrower, the sources said.

news.title: The Economic Times Real Estate Awards 2022-West rewards excellence in industry
news.para: The Economic Times Real Estate Conclave & Awards 2022 - West was graced by the presence of chief guest Irfan A Kazi, Chief Investment Officer, SWAMIH Investment Fund.

news.title: Nagpur civic body all set to collect and reuse construction, demolition waste
news.para: The process to appoint private operator for the purpose has been completed in just two days as against the usual 30-45 days, as the state has authorised municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B to act as administrator of the NMC.

news.title: Mumbai police commissioner asks builders not to carry out construction after 10 pm
news.para: People should not face problems due to the construction work. Therefore, the developers should install acoustic barrier sheets at their sites, Pandey told the builders during the meeting.

news.title: Chandigarh administration to discuss high-rises in periphery, ESZ with states
news.para: The decision was taken in a recent meeting chaired by UT adviser Dharam Pal, who also reviewed the status of implementation of Chandigarh Master Plan-2031.

news.title: Construction waste moved in buses, bike and Gypsy in Gurugram: Report
news.para: These were the vehicles that were supposedly used to collect and transport C&D debris in the city, a committee set up by the Municipal Corporation of Gurgaon (MCG) has found in an inquiry to investigate the alleged Rs 50 crore scam.

news.title: Mysuru development body recovers six acres of land worth Rs 120 crore in Vijayanagar
news.para: About 20 sites of 30x40 dimension can be developed in every acre and every site could fetch approximately nearly Rs 1 crore. On average, Muda would get Rs 25 crore for every developed acre.

news.title: Nalgonda plot auction price reduced to Rs 7,000 per square yard
news.para: Collector Prashant Patil said a large number of bidders had shown interest in the auction of the plots which will take place from March 14-17.
